article.headline: Derkack's 21 help Merrimack take down Bucknell 68-52
article.description: — Jordan Derkack had 21 points in Merrimack's 68-52 win against Bucknell on Friday.
article.linkText: Derkack's 21 help Merrimack take down Bucknell 68-52
article.story: NORTH ANDOVER, Mass. -- — Jordan Derkack had 21 points in Merrimack's 68-52 win against Bucknell on Friday. Derkack added six rebounds, seven assists, and five steals for the Warriors (6-7, Northeast Conference). Devon Savage scored 16 points and added five rebounds. Jaylen Stinson shot 4 for 9 (2 for 6 from 3-point range) and 3 of 3 from the free throw line to finish with 13 points. Noah Williamson finished with 14 points and eight rebounds for the Bison (3-9, Patriot League). Bucknell also got 12 points and six rebounds from Jack Forrest. In addition, Elvin Edmonds IV had seven points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
